* 28 June{{snd}}28 June: Twenty-five Spanish privateers, aboard a sloop, surprise merchant captain Roger Groves (of New York), with 30 to 40 men, in the Bay.{{sfn|''anon.''|1731c}}{{sfn|''anon.''|1731d}}
